She has been also found guilty of violating the provisions of the Executives Ethics Code of the Constitution. In her report, Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane has asked President Cyril Ramaphosa to take appropriate action against Brown within a period of no later than 14 days. Mkhwebane sent her report to the Democratic Alliance (DA) Thursday who was the complainant in the matter. 
Meanwhile, DA is calling on President Cyril Ramaphosa to act siwftly and fire Public Enterprises Minister Lynne Brown. 

Brown failed to disclose that there were the contracts of engagement concluded between Eskom and Gupta linked Triilian.

